description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for enthusiastic, dedicated Band 5 Endoscopy Nurse. The post holders will be required to work Trustwide, working flexibly over weekends and on-call as required by the service. This post is full time (37.5 hours per week) and is based at Hexham General Hospital, but expected to work between sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Endoscopy Unit Managers and Endoscopy Junior Sisters, the individual will be responsible for; provision of pre-assessment; supporting the training of the junior Endoscopy team; provide cross-site cover as required; provide and plan nursing care, and provide effective communication across the multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition, a contribution to the attainment of JAG Accreditation within the Endoscopy Unit will be expected.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Endoscopy Nurse will be expected to attend a number of key meetings as directed, such as the Endoscopy User Group and Endoscopy Governance Group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have a strong engagement approach and be able to demonstrate:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to work with a multi-disciplinary team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An understanding of Trust quality standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to take part in the on-call requirement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work across all sites as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;First level live NMC Registered Nurse&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentorship qualification or relevant qualification (essential requirement for post, expectation this will be completed within an 18 month period)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thorough understanding of contemporary nursing issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring the delivery of ‘Compassion in Practice’- Nursing, Midwifery and Care Staff Vision and Strategy incorporating the 6C’s&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful post holder must be able to role model compassionate and inclusive leadership to shape the creation of a collective leadership culture within the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 18th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
